    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! You honestly won't find another one like this. This beauty has been my absolute pride and joy, kept in a climate-controlled garage and polished more often than I've driven it! It looks and smells brand new\u2014seriously, not a single scratch or smudge anywhere. I\u2019m only letting it go because I need something a bit bigger for the family, but I\u2019m sure it\u2019ll make its next owner super happy. Come take a look, you\u2019re going to fall in love!",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in impeccable condition. This chassis is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been fully overhauled for peak volumetric efficiency. Power is delivered through a crisp ZF 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M differential lock. This example is mechanically superior, featuring documented rod bearing replacement and a reinforced rear subframe to address common structural fatigue points. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications, providing the telepathic feedback and lateral grip these icons are known for. Every bushing, seal, and fluid line is in top-tier order, making this a turn-key acquisition for the serious collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
